Scenario:\'a0During an e-commerce sale event, millions of users log in. While average traffic is manageable, sudden and extreme traffic spikes cause server queues to overflow, crashing the system.\
Goal:\'a0Design server capacity ($C$) not for "average" load, but for extreme "tail" spikes.\
